ALGOWIKI AI
An Intelligent Algorithm Chatbot
1. Introduction
With the increasing demand for quick and reliable information, intelligent chatbot systems
have become essential tools in education and learning. AlgoWiki AI is a lightweight, webbased chatbot designed to provide concise explanations of common search algorithms using
Wikipedia as a knowledge source.
The application leverages Python, Streamlit, and the Wikipedia API to create an interactive
platform where users can ask questions about algorithms like BFS, DFS, A*, and more, and
receive instant summaries.
2. Objectives
The main objectives of this project are:
• To develop an interactive chatbot for algorithm-related queries
• To integrate real-time knowledge retrieval using Wikipedia
• To provide concise and accurate summaries of algorithms
• To design a clean and user-friendly web interface
• To demonstrate the use of APIs and UI frameworks in Python
3. Scope of the Project
This project focuses on:
• Search algorithms such as:
o Breadth-First Search (BFS)
o Depth-First Search (DFS)
o A* Search
o AO* Algorithm
o Hill Climbing
o Best-First Search
• Educational use for students and beginners
• Web-based deployment using Streamlit
Limitations:
• Limited to predefined algorithms
• Relies on Wikipedia summaries (not deep explanations)
• Basic keyword-based query handling
4. System Architecture
The system consists of three main components:
1. User Interface (UI)
• Built using Streamlit
• Accepts user queries
• Displays chatbot responses and history
2. Chatbot Logic Layer
• Handles user input
• Matches keywords with predefined algorithm mappings
• Calls Wikipedia API
3. Data Source
• Wikipedia API provides real-time summaries
